{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Problem\nMigrate the code_health size metrics off the hardcoded `src/rebar` scan + `.github/module-size-limit.txt` onto the scc LOC analyzer + `[code_health]` config, so a non-Python client gets honest Unavailable instead of fabricated zeros. Does NOT touch the CI module-size GATE (separate governance).\n\n## Mechanism (G6 — grounded in the existing registry adapter; positive rationale)\nThe registry wires metrics via a single-arg context adapter `_spec(id, fn, ranged)` whose `compute(ctx)` reads `ctx.repo_root` (+since/until) and calls `fn(...)`. This ticket adds a parallel ANALYZER adapter and reworks the size fns:\n1. `_analyzer_spec(id, fn)`: its `compute(ctx)` obtains the aggregate LOC by calling the scc LOC analyzer `scc_loc.analyze(ctx.repo_root, ctx.scan_roots)` `[rebar:18f9-5b75-b909-408c]` (module size is POLYGLOT aggregate LOC, so it uses the single language-agnostic LOC analyzer directly — NOT `resolve_analyzer(lang)`, which is for per-language complexity/duplication). If `analyze` returns `Unavailable`, `compute` returns `None` (-> the registry renders Unavailable). Otherwise it calls `fn(analyzer_result.loc, ctx.size_cap, ctx.size_near_fraction)` — a UNIFORM 3-arg call; every registered fn takes exactly `(loc, size_cap, size_near_fraction)` (oversized_module_count ignores the last). Rationale: mirrors `_spec`, keeps analyzer invocation in one adapter; using the LOC analyzer directly (vs per-language resolve) matches the polyglot aggregate nature of size metrics.\n2. Config onto ctx: `_commands/metrics.py` (today builds `ctx = SimpleNamespace(repo_root, since, until)`) is extended to also set `scan_roots`, `size_cap`, `size_near_fraction` from the `[code_health]` config `[rebar:e7a0-acef-ec67-42bb]`.\n3. Fns over the loc payload (`loc = {\"files\": {path:int}, \"max_loc\": int}`, shape from `[rebar:18f9-5b75-b909-408c]`):\n   - `module_size_distribution(loc, size_cap, size_near_fraction) -> {\"count\",\"near_cap_count\",\"over_cap_count\",\"max_loc\"}`: count=len(files); max_loc=loc[\"max_loc\"]. If `size_cap is None`: over_cap_count and near_cap_count are `None` (no cap configured -> not computable); else over_cap_count=#files>size_cap, near_cap_count=#files in [size_cap*(1-size_near_fraction), size_cap].\n   - `oversized_module_count(loc, size_cap, size_near_fraction) -> int | None` (UNIFORM 3-arg signature to match the adapter call in §1; `size_near_fraction` is accepted but unused): #files>size_cap, or `None` when `size_cap is None` (-> Unavailable).\n4. Remove `_LIMIT_FILE`/`_read_cap`/the `src/rebar` rglob from git_metrics. DEREGISTER `cap_change_events` (remove from `register()`). REMOVE the `oversized_module_count` SEED MetricSpec (registry.py:142-149, `compute=_no_data_yet`) so git_metrics' real spec is the only one; `module_size_trend` seed (registry.py:134-141) STAYS as a stub returning **Unavailable** (a scc-based snapshot WRITER to feed a trend series does not exist — OUT OF SCOPE / follow-up); `commit_cadence_trend` seed is untouched.\n5. PROVENANCE (T8): the analyzer-derived `module_size_distribution` / `oversized_module_count` MetricSpec entries carry `source=\"structural\"`, `lens=\"code_health\"`.\n\n## Grounding (E4 — verified via Read)\n- CONFIRMED git_metrics.py `_LIMIT_FILE`:35, `_read_cap`:75, `src/rebar` rglob :93, `cap_change_events`:167 registered ~:272; `_spec`/`register` in the registry-integration region (compute(ctx) reads ctx.repo_root/since/until).\n- CONFIRMED registry.py: `module_size_trend` seed :134-141, `oversized_module_count` seed :142-149 (`compute=_no_data_yet`) — the latter is REMOVED here.\n- CONFIRMED `_commands/metrics.py` builds `ctx = SimpleNamespace(repo_root, since, until)` (extended here).\n- Contracts: scc `scc_loc.analyze` + loc payload `[rebar:18f9-5b75-b909-408c]`; `AnalyzerResult`/`Unavailable(reason, accruing_since)` `[rebar:3b30-2168-ba16-41fc]`; config keys `size_cap:int|None`/`size_near_fraction:float`/`scan_roots:list[str]` `[rebar:e7a0-acef-ec67-42bb]` (all depends_on edges recorded).\n- OLD-behavior tests to update: `tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics.py`, `tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics_heldout.py`.\n\n## Acceptance criteria (observable + proving command)\n- [ ] No metric reader references the old hardcodes. PROVE: `! grep -Eq \"src/rebar|module-size-limit.txt\" src/rebar/metrics/git_metrics.py src/rebar/metrics/registry.py`.\n- [ ] Positive path: synthetic `loc={\"files\":{\"a\":100,\"b\":850},\"max_loc\":850}`, size_cap=800 -> module_size_distribution count==2, over_cap_count==1, max_loc==850; oversized_module_count==1. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics.py::test_configured_positive`.\n- [ ] size_cap=None -> over_cap_count/near_cap_count None; oversized_module_count returns None (Unavailable). PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics.py::test_no_cap`.\n- [ ] analyzer-derived specs carry `source=\"structural\"`; the `oversized_module_count` seed stub is removed (only one spec of that id). PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics.py::test_provenance_and_no_dup_seed`.\n- [ ] `cap_change_events` deregistered; `module_size_trend` returns Unavailable. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/interfaces/test_metrics_cli.py::test_cap_change_events_deregistered tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics.py::test_trend_unavailable`.\n- [ ] Unconfigured analyzer (scc_loc.analyze -> Unavailable) -> Unavailable, NOT `{count:0,max_loc:0}` authoritative, no leaked errno. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/interfaces/test_metrics_cli.py::test_foreign_repo_honest_unavailable`.\n- [ ] churn / refactor_to_addition_ratio + agent_process unchanged; updated git_metrics tests green. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics.py tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics_heldout.py`.\n\n## Dependencies: 3b30, 18f9, 21fb, 3ba0, e7a0 (recorded depends_on).\n## Files likely touched\n- src/rebar/metrics/git_metrics.py (add `_analyzer_spec` + reworked fns; remove hardcodes + `cap_change_events`)\n- src/rebar/metrics/registry.py (remove the `oversized_module_count` seed stub)\n- src/rebar/_commands/metrics.py (ctx carries the [code_health] config)\n- tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics.py, tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics_heldout.py, tests/interfaces/test_metrics_cli.py\n## Estimated scope: M-L"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784612452177485001,"uuid":"a8ab3a0a-9d7f-4bc9-a794-126f1805d1d5"}